@startuml
|User|
start
:Navigates to a page that contains an Activity Log view;

|System|
:Validates receiving a scope context;

if (Is the scope context valid?) then (yes)
    :Loads a default filter set for the Activity Log;
    :Sends a petition to the server with scope and filters;
    :Validates the filter values;
else (no)
    |User|
    :Sees an error message informing an invalid Activity Log scope has been selected;
    stop
endif

|System|
if (Are filter values valid?) then (yes)
    :Selects the query to use based on the scope;
    :Sends the corresponding query to the database;
else (no)
    |User|
    :Sees an error message asking to correct the filter values;
    stop
endif

|Database|
:Returns the matching Activity rows;

|System|
:Verifies if any content was received;

if (Is there any information received from the database?) then (yes)
    :Formats the Activity rows into Activity Log cards or table entries;
else (no)
    |User|
    :Sees a message informing there are no Activity entries for the selected scope and date range;
    stop
endif

|System|
if (Did the System receive an error from the server or database?) then (yes)
    |User|
    :Sees an error message informing the Activity Log could not be loaded and is asked to retry;
    stop
else (no)
endif

|User|
:Sees the Activity Log entries;
:Applies filters or changes the date range;

|System|
:Sends a new petition to the server with updated filters;
:Refreshes the Activity Log view with the filtered results;

|User|
:Sees the updated Activity Log entries;
stop
@enduml